Jenkins is an open-source automation tool used to build, test, and deploy software applications.

Here are a few simple lines:
Jenkins helps automate repetitive tasks in the software development lifecycle.
It is widely used for CI/CD (Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery) pipelines.
Jenkins can automatically build and test code whenever changes are pushed to a repository.
It supports integration with tools such as Git, Docker, Ansible, Maven, and cloud platforms.
Jenkins provides thousands of plugins to extend its functionality.
It helps development teams deliver software faster and with fewer errors.
Jenkins can run on Windows, Linux, and macOS environments.

In one sentence: Jenkins is an automation server that helps teams continuously build, test, and deploy applications efficiently.
